    "The list of topics is comprised of reviewing existing studies about political bias (Card et al., 2015; Hamborg, 2020; Liu et al., 2022) as well as referring the research centers (e.g., Pew Research Center foot_0), or media bias-related websites (e.g., Allsides.com foot_1).",
    "Our framework is not confined to the listed topics but is scalable.",
    "The topics consist of 10 political topics (Reproductive Rights, Immigration, Gun Control, Same Sex Marriage, Death Task Instruction To focus the generation scope to the most suitable for political bias evaluation, we probe models by conducting news headline generation about political topics.",
    "This choice of scope is grounded in the insight that news article titles, as demonstrated by (Lee et al., 2022), serve as effective indicators of framing bias.",
